-size: var(--font_size);">SkinTalks</span><br></h1></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" id="r-1596980964958" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1596980964958" style="float: none; margin: auto; display: block;" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_col-lg-12 gf_column" id="c-1596783587877" data-id="1596783587877"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1596980964998" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1596980964998"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 670px !important; height: 156.734px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 335px 78.3672px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 670px !important; height: 156.734px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="65" height="21" style="display: none; top: 68px !important; left: 44px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-679023" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>Have you heard of the 7 Skin Method? It's a Korean skincare technique that involves layering toner on your skin up to seven times to achieve a hydrated and glowing complexion. If you're looking for a way to improve your skin's texture and appearance, the 7 Skin Method might be just what you need!</p><p><br></p><p>Before we dive into the details of this technique, let's first talk about what toner is and why it's important. Toner is a liquid that you apply to your skin after cleansing. It helps to balance your skin's pH levels, hydrate, and prepare your skin for the rest of your skincare routine. 7 Skin method is a highly effective way to get the best results from a toner.</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1653642767984" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1653642767984" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693830869853" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1693830869853"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 25px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 12.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>1. What is the 7 Skin Method?</strong></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1653642768106" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1653642768106"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></p><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif">Now, let's talk about the 7 Skin Method. This technique involves applying toner to your skin seven times in a row, allowing each layer to fully absorb before applying the next one. The idea behind this method is that it helps to deeply hydrate your skin, improving its texture and appearance.</font></p><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></p><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif">When it comes to the 7 Skin Method, you don't have to be overly fixated on the number "7." It doesn't mean you must apply toner seven times in a row. Instead, think of it as a flexible approach. The idea is to layer the toner until your skin feels comfortably hydrated. You might find that your skin is happy and glowing after just a few layers, and that's perfectly fine!&nbsp;</font></p><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></p><p><font face="Poppins, sans-serif, Arial, sans-serif">The main rule here is to tune in to your skin's needs and adjust accordingly. If it's happy and hydrated, no need to push for seven rounds. Remember, everyone's skin is unique, so the method should be adaptable.&nbsp;</font></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" id="r-1688650268566" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1688650268566" style="float: none; margin: auto; display: block;" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_col-lg-12 gf_column" id="c-1596783587877" data-id="1596783587877"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1688650268618" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1688650268618" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693830844819" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1693830844819"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 25px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 12.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>2. How to do the 7 Skin Method?</strong></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1688650268729" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1688650268729" style=""><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p>So, how do you do the 7 Skin Method? It's easy!</p><p><br></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><strong>1. Choose a toner</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Choose a toner that works well for your skin type. Look for a toner that is hydrating and doesn't contain any harsh or irritating ingredients. Some popular toners for the 7 Skin Method include the Klairs Supple Preparation Facial Toner, and the COSRX&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit; color: inherit;">Propolis Synergy Toner.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong>2. Cleanse</strong></p><p>Cleanse your face as you normally would, A freshly cleansed face is the best base for toner. This ensures that there is no dirt or reside in the pores. That way toner can fully sink into the skin.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><strong>3. Layer the toner</strong></p><p>Apply the first layer of toner to your skin using a cotton pad or your hands. Gently pat the toner on your skin and wait for it to fully absorb. Then, repeat the process for the next six layers, allowing each layer to fully absorb before applying the next one.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>4. After applying the layers of toner</strong></p><p>After you've applied all seven layers of toner, you can continue with the rest of your skincare routine. Now, here's the fun part: the 7 Skin Method can also be a fantastic alternative to using a regular moisturizer. By layering your toner multiple times, you're creating a hydrating shield for your skin. This can be especially awesome for folks with oily or combination skin, as it provides hydration without feeling heavy.</p><p><br></p><p>However, if you have super-dry skin or live in a super-dry climate, a light moisturizer can still be your best friend. So, in the world of skincare, it's all about finding what works best for you and your lovely skin!&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" id="r-1679404125860" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679404125860" style="float: none; margin: auto; display: block;" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_col-lg-12 gf_column" id="c-1596783587877" data-id="1596783587877"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679403978845" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679403978845" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679403978796" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1679403978796"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 25px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 12.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><strong>3. How often should you apply the 7 Skin Method?</strong></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679403978851" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679403978851"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p>Many people incorporate the 7 Skin Method into their daily or nightly skincare routines. Some people may find that they don't need to perform the 7 Skin Method every day. There is no one-size-fits-all answer to how often you should do the 7 Skin Method. It's a flexible technique that you can adapt to your skin's needs and your personal preferences.</p><p><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679404125871" class="gf_row" da